Recent political gatherings have been dominated by songs praising presidential hopefuls Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa and Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) Secretary General Gwede Mantashe says the party's delegates at the upcoming national policy conference will not be allowed to sing divisive songs or those praising their preferred candidates for ANC President.The party has given an update on preparations on the eve of its policy conference.Recent ANC and alliance partners political gatherings have been dominated by songs praising presidential hopefuls Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa and Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma.Gwede Mantashe says such songs won't be allowed at this conference. We re not confused about songs, we know established songs about the movement. We will not tamper with them because there is a conference. However, he says songs praising President Jacob Zuma will be permitted but those denigrating him won't.WATCH: #ANCNPC No divisive songs may be sung(Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)